<HEAD>Heavy Rain in Arkansas; Flooding in Pennsylvania</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms dumped rain from northern Arkansas to the Ohio
Valley today and a cool front brought showers to the northern
Rockies.
   A 2-inch downpour fell in an hour at White Pine, Pa., Monday
night, and basements and roads flooded near Frostburg, Clarysville
and Eckhart.
   About three quarters of an inch fell in Fayetteville, Ark., and
Harrison reported more than half an inch.
   Warm moist air produced thunderstorms over New Mexico and
northwest Texas. A cold front moving across the northern Rockies
generated showers and thunderstorms from western Montana into
northern Idaho.
   Showers and thunderstorms also extended from the central
Appalachians to the coast of the Carolinas.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from much
of Arizona and New Mexico across the southern Rockies to much of
Texas; from Florida across the Tennessee Valley; and in southern
Missouri, the lower Ohio Valley and southern portions of the Great
Lakes.
   Highs were expected to be in the 70s along the Pacific Coast;
the 80s from the southern and central Rockies across portions of
the Plains and the Mississippi Valley to the upper Great Lakes;
from 100 to 115 degrees from central California through the Desert
Southwest; and in the 90s elsewhere.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 50 degrees at
Yellowstone, Wyo., to 95 degrees at Glendale, Ariz., and Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 74 fair; Boston 71 foggy; Buffalo 70 foggy;
Charleston, S.C. 77 thunderstorms; Cincinnati 72 foggy; Cleveland
71 hazy; Detroit 73 hazy; Miami 79 partly cloudy; New York 71 fair;
Philadelphia 73 hazy; Pittsburgh 73 hazy; Portland, Maine 66
cloudy; Washington 78 hazy.
   _Central: Bismarck 74 fair; Chicago 72 foggy; Dallas-Fort Worth
73 fair; Denver 63 fair; Des Moines 71 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
71 foggy; Kansas City 67 foggy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 71 foggy;
Nashville 73 fair; New Orleans 73 showers; St. Louis 75 foggy.
