<SECOND>AM-BRF--Korea-Bodies,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Bodies Believed to be North Korean Soldiers Found in River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two bodies believed to be those of
North Korean soldiers were found in the Imjin River near the
demilitarized zone, police said Wednesday.
   Kim Tok-gu of the village of Songok told police he found a body
in a North Korean uniform Monday in the river. Another body was
found six hours later farther downstream, police said.
   The bodies would be turned over to military authorities, police
said.
   Bodies of North Koreans, presumably drowning victims,
occasionally float down rivers during the season of heavy rains and
floods.
