<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SAfrica-Mine     07-25 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--SAfrica-Mine,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>10 Killed in Rush of Water</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A rush of water at the bottom
of a gold mine shaft Tuesday killed 10 miners and injured three,
mining officials said.
   Gold Fields of South Africa Ltd. said it is investigating the
origin of the water flow at the bottom of the 6,600-foot No. 1
shaft at Kloof Gold Mine.
   The men were caught by the water as they were walking up a
steeply inclined tunnel, said mine spokesman Attie Roets. He said
the water would not have been a natural phenomenon that deep
underground.
   The Kloof mine near Westonaria, about 30 miles southwest of
Johannesburg, employs about 17,500 men.
