the House voted to cut Star Wars spending to $3.1 billion, $1.8
billion below President Bush's request and $700 million below the
level recommended by the Armed Services Committee.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to cut the money.
   Voting yes were 214 Democrats and 34 Republicans.
   Voting no were 38 Democrats and 137 Republicans.
   Y is yes. N is no. X denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are 3 vacancies in the 435-member House.
