<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's hens shelled out an estimated
5.48 billion eggs in June, down 2 percent from a year earlier, the
Agriculture Department said Tuesday.
   Figures by the department's National Agricultural Statistics
Service showed the reduction reflected a cutback in the number of
birds in the U.S. laying flock, which averaged 266 million in June,
also down 2 percent.
   The rate of lay in June was reported at 2,060 eggs per 100 hens,
compared with 2,053 in June 1988.
