<HEAD>Cuomo Makes Ladybug State Insect</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ROBERT BELLAFIORE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ladybug, ladybug, New York is your home.
   Your fame is ensured, the job has been done.
   Gov'nor Cuomo says you're his bug _ you alone.
   Ladybug, ladybug, New York is your home.
   
   Good Gov'nor Cuomo has ruled on a bill.
   It makes you state insect, oh what a thrill!
   The bluebird, the beaver, the rose and the trout,
   They've all gone 'ere you for New Yorkers to tout.
   
   Ladybug, ladybug, good company you suit
   With apples for muffins and as fruit to boot.
   Garnet as gem, sugar maples as trees
   And fossil Eurypterus, a scorpion of seas.
   
   New York is your land, where milk is the choice
   Empire for beetles, even you have a voice.
   You've earned your new title, your honorable nom;
   Excelsior! little ladybug, good rest in your home.
