<FIRST>r a AM-DaughterBurned     07-25 0249</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Daughter Burned,0259</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Charged with Setting Pregnant Daughter on Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pregnant 18-year-old woman who police say
was set on fire during an argument with her father gave birth to a
healthy baby Tuesday. She suffered burns over 70 percent of her
body.
   Kimberly Richmond was in serious condition Tuesday at Children's
Medical Hospital in Akron with third-degree burns. She gave birth
to a 4{-pound girl by Caesarean section, said hospital spokeswoman
Carol Wallace.
   Police Capt. Jerry Foys said the woman's father, Joseph
Richmond, 41, was arrested without incident at the hospital and
charged with felonious assault. He was in the Summit County jail on
$2,500 cash bond following arraignment.
   A preliminary hearing was set for Wednesday.
   ``The father said he didn't mean to burn her. He merely meant to
scare her,'' said police Maj. Leonard Strawderman. ``After that, he
wouldn't give any more information.''
   Foys said police do not know what father and daughter argued
about Monday night.
   ``He (Richmond) went and got some flammable liquid _ we think it
was brake fluid _ and poured it onto the girl and set her afire,''
Foys said.
   Strawderman said Ms. Richmond is single and lives with her
parents.
   ``She didn't really give a statement to authorities,''
Strawderman said, adding that investigators could not interview her
because of her condition.
   Ms. Wallace said the baby appeared healthy.
   ``The baby's in great shape. She's a little small but she's
doing really well,'' Ms. Wallace said.
</TEXT>
