<FIRST>r i AM-Britain-B17     07-25 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Britain-B17,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ten Survive as Bomber Crashes During Filming</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BINBROOK, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A World War II-vintage B17 bomber being
used in a movie starring American actors Matthew Modine and John
Lithgow crashed during filming Tuesday but all 10 people aboard
survived, the Royal Air Force said.
   The Flying Fortress hit a tree while attempting to take off from
an old air force base in Lincolnshire and broke apart in a field.
   The most serious injury was a broken leg, said a spokesman for
Enigma Films, which is making the movie. Two people, who were not
identified, were admitted to a hospital, and eight others were
treated for minor injuries.
   The B17 was one of five used in the film ``The Memphis Belle,''
produced by David Puttnam and starring Modine, Lithgow and Eric
Stolz. None of the stars was aboard the aircraft, the air force
said.
</TEXT>
