<FIRST>r f PM-JeepProduction     07-25 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Jeep Production,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report: Chrysler to Put Jeep `JJ' in Toledo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. will begin producing a small
sport-utility vehicle in its Toledo, Ohio, plant in mid-1993, an
automotive trade journal reported.
   Ward's Automotive Reports quoted sources Monday as saying
Chrysler's Stickney Avenue plant would be the site for production
of the `JJ,'' a vehicle the company plans to build in a joint
venture with the French automaker Renault.
   Chrysler Chairman Lee Iacocca announced both the joint venture
and the ``JJ'' project earlier this year. He said some of the
vehicles would be made in Europe and some would be made in North
America but declined to be more specific.
   Chrysler spokeswoman Karen Stewart declined to comment on the
Ward's report.
</TEXT>
