<SECOND>BC-Earns-Borden,0186</SECOND>
<HEAD>Borden Earnings Rise 13.9 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Borden Inc. said Tuesday that second-quarter
earnings rose 13.9 percent in spite of continued declines in its
dairy operations.
   Borden Chairman R.J. Ventres cited what he called strong steady
growth in many other businesses, in particular pasta, snacks,
certain grocery items, and domestic films and adhesives.
   New York-based Borden's earnings rose to $83.9 million, or $1.13
a share, from $73.7 million, or $1 a share, a year earlier. Revenue
rose 5.1 percent to $1.87 billion from $1.78 billion.
   For the first half, Borden said earnings rose 13.4 percent to
$143 million, or $1.93 a share, from $126.1 million, or $1.71 a
share, a year earlier. Revenue rose 8.6 percent to $3.68 billion
from $3.39 billion.
   Operating income in the dairy division fell 15.4 percent, but
the decline was less than half the 36 percent decline reported in
the first quarter of the year. Still, the company said ``intense
price competition continues in the industry, and another increase
in raw milk costs is expected in the third quarter.''
</TEXT>
