<FIRST>r f BC-EntertainmentGroup     07-25 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Entertainment Group,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>MCEG Plans To Buy London-Based Distributor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Independent film producer Management Company
Entertainment Group Inc. said it plans to purchase London-based
film distributor Virgin Vision Ltd. for $83 million.
   The acquisition would greatly expand the operations of the
5-year-old MCEG in the lucrative overseas markets, giving it access
to a film library that includes the United Kingdom rights to such
Orion movies as ``Robocop.''
   MCEG plans to buy Virgin Vision from parent company Virgin Group
Ltd. with $55 million in cash and $7.5 million in debt.
   In addition, Virgin Group will receive 5.4 million shares of
MCEG stock at $3.75 per share, making Virgin Group the largest
minority shareholder of MCEG, the company said.
   MCEG, involved in film production, marketing and talent
management, released ``The Chocolate War.'' Its upcoming releases
include ``Convicts'' with Robert Duvall and ``Boardwalk'' with
Sally Kellerman.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
